[France maintains -- since December 2000 -- the status of a country "officially bTB free" according to OIE's international criteria ("at least 99.8 percent of the herds free"). Herd surveillance has been applied in areas with historical background and in herds with high potential for spread (such as raw milk dairy farms).

Three potential wild bTB reservoirs are suspected in France -- wild boar, red deer, and badger. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2641321,14066.]
